<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Description">Description</span></h2>
<pre><b>persist_id = persist_add(key, initial_value)</b>
</pre>
<p><b>persist_add</b> is used to create a new persistence object. Data provided to a persistence object will remain between sessions.
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Return_value">Return value</span></h2>
<table class="wikitable">

<tbody><tr>
<th>Argument</th>
<th>Type</th>
<th>Description
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td><b>persist_id</b></td>
<td><i>ID</i></td>
<td>This value can be used for further reference. Functions such as <a href="/index.php?title=Persist_get" title="Persist get">persist_get</a> and <a href="/index.php?title=Persist_put" title="Persist put">persist_put</a> can use this persist_id. Its good practice to store this persist_id in your logic code.
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Arguments">Arguments</span></h2>
<table class="wikitable">

<tbody><tr>
<th>#</th>
<th>Argument</th>
<th>Type</th>
<th>Description
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>1</td>
<td><b>key</b></td>
<td><i>String</i></td>
<td>Unique identifier key to be able to keep different persistence objects separated.
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>2</td>
<td><b>initial_value</b></td>
<td><i>Object</i></td>
<td>The initial value of the persistence object. This value will be used when no data is yet available. This argument is optional, when not used, the data is typically initialized with all zero's.
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Example">Example</span></h2>
<pre><code class="lua todo">-- Create a new persistence obeject
persist_id = persist_add(&quot;mykey&quot;, { 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8 })

-- Get the data from the persistence object
mydata = persist_get(persist_id)

-- Put new data into the persistence object
persist_put(persist_id, { 8, 7, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1 } )</code></pre><script type="">if('hljsGo' in window) window.hljsGo();</script>
